oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Capitol of the "State of Franklin," Greeneville, Tennessee
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Capitol structure of the "State of Franklin," an attempted community of settlers from Virginia and North Carolina who hoped to settle in the area which became East Tennessee.
The men who established the State of Franklin did not have the backing of North Carolina or Virginia. They also had to contend with the Native Americans who felt that the land belonged to them.
